cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper discusses user-generated content-sharing online communities and introduces metrics to quantify the level of collaboration among users. It also discusses the implications of these findings in the context of recommendation and reputation systems. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
